The paper deals with the problem of inverse reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves function approximation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The method is designed to handle high-dimensional state spaces, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions using the method to evaluate a doctor's proficiency, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for analyzing medical images or videos.
